<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id56b95060-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02" identifier="/us/usc/t14/s2124"><num value="2124">§ 2124.</num><heading> Promotions; pay and allowances</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">An officer who is promoted under <ref href="/us/usc/t14/s2121">section 2121 of this title</ref> shall be entitled to the pay and allowances of the grade to which promoted from his date of rank in such grade.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id56b95061-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/88/130/s1/10/C">Pub. L. 88–130, § 1(10)(C)</ref>, <date date="1963-09-24">Sept. 24, 1963</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/77/182">77 Stat. 182</ref>, § 274; renumbered § 2124 and amended <ref href="/us/pl/115/282/tI">Pub. L. 115–282, title I</ref>, §§ 112(b), 123(b)(2), <date date="2018-12-04">Dec. 4, 2018</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/132/4216">132 Stat. 4216</ref>, 4240.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id56b95062-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02">
